  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of international and national regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n- Counter-terrorism financing regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Regulatory sanctions\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- National financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n6. Compliance Obligations:\n- Financial institutions\n- Designated non-financial businesses\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Professional service providers\n\nThis framework aims to prevent criminal financial activities and maintain financial system integrity.",
